{"image_id": "PMC4619733_7", "image_size": [773, 1000], "ocr": [{"text": "Future Distribution of Rhynchophorus ferrugineus in China", "bbox": [473.7, 48.8, 727.3, 60.9]}, {"text": "Table 1. CLIMEX parameter values for Rhynchophorus ferrugineus.", "bbox": [45.5, 95.4, 360.5, 108.0]}, {"text": "CLIMEX parameter Wet tropical template Desert template Temperate template Final parameter", "bbox": [45.5, 116.1, 727.4, 128.0]}, {"text": "DVO-Lower temperature threshold 15 15 8 10.3", "bbox": [45.5, 135.4, 672.5, 146.9]}, {"text": "DV1-Lower optimum temperature 26 25 18 28", "bbox": [45.5, 151.1, 664.2, 162.7]}, {"text": "DV2-Upper optimum temperature 33 40 24 32", "bbox": [45.5, 166.9, 664.2, 178.5]}, {"text": "DV3-Upper temperature threshold 36 44 28 40", "bbox": [45.5, 182.7, 664.2, 194.3]}, {"text": "PDD-Effective accumulated temperature 0 0 600 1100", "bbox": [45.5, 198.5, 675.3, 210.1]}, {"text": "TTCS-Cold stress temperature threshold 0 2 0 –2.3", "bbox": [45.5, 214.3, 672.4, 225.8]}, {"text": "THCS-Cold stress temperature rate 0 0.001 0 0.05", "bbox": [45.5, 230.1, 672.5, 241.6]}, {"text": "TTHS-Heat stress temperature threshold 36 44 30 44", "bbox": [45.5, 245.8, 664.2, 257.4]}, {"text": "THHS-Heat stress temperature rate 0.001 0.001 0.005 0.001", "bbox": [45.5, 261.6, 678.1, 273.1]}, {"text": "SMO-Lower soil moisture threshold 0.3 0 0.25 0", "bbox": [45.5, 277.4, 658.6, 289.0]}, {"text": "SM1-Lower optimal soil moisture 0.5 0.001 0.8 0.5", "bbox": [45.5, 293.1, 666.9, 304.7]}, {"text": "SM2-Upper optimal soil moisture 1.75 0.2 1.5 1.75", "bbox": [45.5, 309.0, 672.5, 320.5]}, {"text": "SM3-Upper soil moisture threshold 2 0.3 2.5 2", "bbox": [45.5, 324.7, 658.6, 336.3]}, {"text": "SMDS-Dry stress threshold 0.3 0 0.2 0", "bbox": [45.5, 340.5, 658.6, 352.1]}, {"text": "HDS-Dry stress rate 0.006 0 0.005 0.006", "bbox": [45.5, 356.3, 678.1, 367.8]}, {"text": "SMWS-Wet stress threshold 2 0.3 2.5 2", "bbox": [45.5, 372.1, 658.6, 383.7]}, {"text": "HWS-Wet stress rate 0.002 0.1 0.002 0.002", "bbox": [45.5, 387.8, 678.1, 399.4]}, {"text": "doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0141111.t001", "bbox": [45.5, 407.6, 184.7, 418.9]}, {"text": "reference when setting the dry (wet) SI. However, R. ferrugineus is highly adaptable and sur-", "bbox": [252.5, 437.1, 711.4, 451.0]}, {"text": "vives in dry environments with a measure of drought tolerance, as reported in Libya and Egypt", "bbox": [252.5, 453.5, 724.1, 467.4]}, {"text": "(http://www.cabi.org/). Therefore, the DS threshold (SMDS) was defined as zero after being", "bbox": [252.5, 469.9, 708.9, 483.8]}, {"text": "debugged repeatedly, and the other parameters of dry (wet) stress were in set accordance with", "bbox": [252.5, 486.4, 719.0, 500.3]}, {"text": "the wet tropical template data.", "bbox": [252.5, 502.7, 403.6, 516.7]}, {"text": "The temperature indices were debugged according to the actual distribution using biological", "bbox": [267.6, 519.1, 726.8, 533.1]}, {"text": "data as references. Based on the experimental results of Li [35] and Salama et al. [37], the opti-", "bbox": [252.5, 535.6, 721.7, 549.5]}, {"text": "mum temperature range (DV1–DV2) was defined as 28–32°C, with the upper temperature", "bbox": [252.5, 552.0, 704.8, 565.9]}, {"text": "Fig 3. Predicting results for Rhynchophorus ferrugineus created by CLIMEX.", "bbox": [45.5, 869.5, 401.8, 882.2]}, {"text": "doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0141111.g003", "bbox": [45.5, 889.6, 187.0, 901.0]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | DOI:10.1371/journal.pone.0141111 October 23, 2015 8 / 26", "bbox": [45.5, 945.2, 727.3, 956.7]}]}